  "updated_summary": "The Pink Dragon, with glowing yellow eyes and sharp teeth, roars a declaration of impending darkness, stating, \"There is no escape, Metal Man. Soon, the night will shine no more,\" before spreading its red wings against a pink cosmic backdrop and cutting to black. A whooshing sound, zapping effects, and a crash transition the scene to a bright, futuristic living room where Robin, Raven, Starfire, and Beast Boy are found sprawled and dazed. Starfire questions their location, and Robin confirms their return but notes Cyborg's absence, leading Starfire to panic that he is trapped in the dimension of the Nightshines. Beast Boy insists they must go back for him, but Robin explains the only way in is through the power of a specific song. Beast Boy, determined, attempts to sing the song off-key with great effort, \"When I look at you... I see the story in your eyes... When you're dancing... The night begins to shine... The night begins to shine, no!\" Raven expresses exasperation with a sigh, and Beast Boy, crying and kneeling, questions why it isn't working. Robin, kneeling beside him, deadpans that it's likely because he \"sing[s] like garbage.\" Starfire, placing a comforting hand on Raven's shoulder, explains that the song was made from magic, and that magic is the key."
